\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}',13,1,'','',1,30,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}',0,'en-GB',''),(122,235,'HISTORY','history','<h5>GOODBYE AFRICA</h5>\r\n<p>The title of a film for an Hollywood life or almost.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe dynasty that we are going to speak about today is an adventurous one: people without fear and with great spirit of initiative, strong people, tenacious people, from good roots around Veneto-Lombard. Today we are speaking about the Lorenzetto family, floriculturists, raised as farmers in Veneto at the beginning of the century.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nNereo Lorenzetto, son of a hard-working couple of farmers in Veneto-Lombard, grew up in the earths love, cultivated the ground and lived in Padova where he got married and started to rear his own family. In this very particular time for our country, Arrigo was born.\r\n</p>\r\n','\r\n<p>\r\nOn an African beach in Lybia, which was part of the Italian Terza Sponda  3rd Bank, you could find fabulous work prospects for men with audacious and open minded spirits; Nereo and his family decided to go and see\r\n \r\nAt this time it wasnt that easy as Libya was just starting to develop. But where youth and optimism are, everything is possible. And it proved to be a very good move. Nereo received 5/600 hectares of good soil. Corn, Olives and Tobacco were produced and sold with a good profit. This led them, without any doubt, to stay and initiate building for the future, starting with the children.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nFrom 1935 onwards, 5 children were born and the ground was always fertile and the trade satisfactory. Sadly, Italy lost the war. Few words seemed to be adequate to describe this period of unrest which was so crucial for so many people\r\nThe shock wave created by this devastating situation in our country violently invaded the Terza Sponda  3rd Bank and the Lorenzetto Family. Their ground was required. And the British came to govern Lybia.\r\nThis must have been, indeed, a tough and dangerous period of time, when simple things were overlooked with suspicion and animosity. Arrigo was a young man and because he didnt want to undergo the situation he fled. Attached with an incredible strength to the hawser of a boat which was weighing up the anchor, (Oh my God what a scary moment!), he reached, with Gods help, Naples, where the sentence starting from scratch seemed to enter the family blazon.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nLife was hard and full of adventures, and the problems didnt take long to occur. The Italian government caught him without his papers. No choice: the national military service was compulsory. Luckily the war was over!\r\nAlone, in a country that he hardly knew, the family still settled far away in now unfriendly surroundings It was not easy but he was very strong-willed. Maybe the future will be full of fascinating promises Once his dues were paid to the state and well aware of the few immediate prospects that his tortured country could offer, he emigrated to France and found a job as a farm machine driver in Nice. The job was pleasant and the weather quite nice, but it was not what Arrigo was expecting. He wanted more. The future was calling him, and Arrigo, always looking for better, left for Germany. Germany still had so much to rebuild, there was work and he met Caterina.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nLife went on but the news from Africa was not comforting. The heart of the Lorenzetto Family was going through hard times. Lybia was affected by clamour and civilian war, and the situation of the ex colonies was becoming worse and painful. Nereo Lorenzetto was slowly expelled from the soil he had worked on for so many years and from where he had grown up with his family. A sad day, the story comes to an end. The soil is lost for ever there only remains life even if dangerously uncertain. It is a hard reality, unfair and cruel. God hadnt heard their voices this time.\r\nThank God Nereo has his home country. His roots were in Italy and with his family he fled. And again he started from scratch. Arrigo and his brothers were now united by a common goal. Albenga received the tired family and offered to young and strong arms a possibility of renewal. Meanwhile in Germany, Arrigo and Caterina were happy to celebrate the birth of Germano, third generation of an adventurous lineage.\r\nThey lived quite well in this big country despite the cold weather but the homesickness was getting stronger and stronger and Arrigo finally went back to Albenga. They were all reunited! Half of the 1960s see the Lorenzetto brothers cultivating rented ground which produced vegetables exported to Sweden and Germany. Working hard, they managed to buy a domain  which will later be sold in order to give the possibility for each new family unit to start over on its own. And again  we start from scratch.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nSlowly but surely the ground gave its fruits. They worked, saved and went on buying pieces of land in Liguria. Arrigo decided then to build a green house. A strong believer in life, throwing all his energy into it, he believed he would make a go of it. And he made it! He cultivated tomatoes and placed them well on the local market but it wasnt enough for him.\r\n \r\nThe young Germano and with him the fair ambitions of his father could be the title of the next adventure In the 1970s, Arrigo built a new green house, not alone anymore, and gave a decisive curve to his business. He started growing Barberton Daisy for cutting sale purposes. New work, new experiences and a lot of satisfaction. The middle way seemed to be found For the young company, around 4 years old, new and attractive prospects were arising..\r\n \r\nThey grew Dracaenas of various types, Yucca from Guatemala and Costarica in the green house; and Eucalyptus outside. And they still had some free landThis idea pleased Germano who started working hand to hand with Daddy Arrigo, and constantly developed the company. The project was taking form and the transformation of the growings was developing, together with the participation at various exhibitions ( Flormart in Padova, Miflor in Milan).\r\n \r\nAfter all these adventures we now reach the present time.\r\n \r\nThe company Lorenzetto SAS that we know today is made up of 20,000 square metres of nurseries and 20,000 square metres of open ground. In the nurseries they grow some typical Mediterranean plants in pots, such as: Cyclamen, Christmas Star and Chrysanthemum in Autumn; and Lantana, Blue Potato Bush and Daisy in Spring. The open ground is dedicated to the most appreciated variety of Italian aromatics, famous all over Europe.\r\nThe merging of logistic opportunities together with over 20 years of joint work with 240 other farms has contributed to expand their selection and therefore their capacity to satisfy the request of their customers anytime.\r\n \r\nThanks to the market orientated business of the Lorenzetto SAS, the company is also able to supply a wide range of Sicilian plants, for which they have two main storage areas, one in Albenga and the other in Messina, in order to be able to dispatch orders directly from the production site: Paper flower, Bottlebrush, Citrus ( orange, lemon, tangerine, kumquat ), Oleander, Canary Island Date Palm and Cycas  available in all kinds of shapes and sizes.\r\n \r\nThat is why the Lorenzetto SAS has become a leading exporting producer in the international market of potted plants, working with big names.\r\nThey are also focused on advanced research and a constant development of the floriculture system of production, as well as a winning pricing policy. Elements which allow them to offer quality products with the best guarantee of an efficient and reliable service. Here is what they can offer you.\r\n</p>',1,12,'2014-01-02 13:20:03',591,'','0000-00-00 00:00:00',0,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2014-01-02 13:20:03','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_caption\":\"\"}','{\"urla\":false,\"urlatext\":\"\",\"targeta\":\"\",\"urlb\":false,\"urlbtext\":\"\",\"targetb\":\"\",\"urlc\":false,\"urlctext\":\"\",\"targetc\":\"\"}','{\"show_title\":\"\",\"link_titles\":\"\",\"show_tags\":\"\",\"show_intro\":\"\",\"info_block_position\":\"\",\"show_category\":\"\",\"link_category\":\"\",\"show_parent_category\":\"\",\"link_parent_category\":\"\",\"show_author\":\"\",\"link_author\":\"\",\"show_create_date\":\"\",\"show_modify_date\":\"\",\"show_publish_date\":\"\",\"show_item_navigation\":\"\",\"show_icons\":\"\",\"show_print_icon\":\"\",\"show_email_icon\":\"\",\"show_vote\":\"\",\"show_hits\":\"\",\"show_noauth\":\"\",\"urls_position\":\"\",\"alternative_readmore\":\"\",\"article_layout\":\"\",\"show_publishing_options\":\"\",\"show_article_options\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_backend\":\"\",\"show_urls_images_frontend\":\"\"}',1,1,'','',1,0,'{\"robots\":\"\",\"author\":\"\",\"rights\":\"\",\"xreference\":\"\"}',0,'en-GB',''),(123,237,'HISTOIRE','histoire','<h5>ADIEU AFRIQUE</h5>\r\n<p>Le titre dun film pour une vie de film... ou presque.</p>\r\n<p>Nous allons parler aujourdhui dune dynastie daventuriers: de gens sans peur et avec un grand esprit dinitiative, de gens forts et tenaces, de bonne souche lombardo-vnitienne.\r\nAujourdhui nous parlons de la famille Lorenzetto, floriculteurs, ne comme agriculteurs en Vntie au dbut de notre sicle.</p>\r\n<p>Nereo Lorenzetto, fils dun couple robuste dagriculteurs lombardo-vnitien, lev dans lamour de la terre la cultive et vit  Padoue, o il se marie et commence  crer sa propre cellule familiale. Nat Arrigo, dans une priode particulire pour notre pays.\r\nSur une plage africaine en Lybie, qui faisait alors partie de la  Terza Sponda  3me Berge  italienne, o il y avait de fabuleuses perspectives de travail pour les hommes aux esprits audacieux et  la mentalit ouverte Nereo, avec sa femme et son fils; dcident daller voir</p>\r\n','\r\n<p>\r\nA cette poque ce ntait pas une mince affaire: ctait mme prcisment un sacr bon en avant. Mais quand il y a la jeunesse et loptimisme, tout semble possible.\r\nEt cela se rvle un choix gagnant. Nereo obtient 5/600 hectares de bonne terre. Mas, Olives, Tabac sont produites et commercialiss avec un bon profit. Sans aucun doute cela les amne  rester et  commencer  construire quelque chose de solide, en commenant par les enfants.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nA partir de 1935 et les annes suivantes, naissent 5 autres enfants et la terre est toujours aussi fertile et le commerce satisfaisant. Malheureusement, lItalie perd la guerre. Comme peu de paroles semblent pertinentes pour dcrire des vnements si solennels et dterminants pour tant de personnes\r\nLonde de choc cre par la situation dsastreuse de notre pays envahi violemment la  Terza Sponda  3me Berge, et la famille Lorenzetto. Leur terre est rquisitionne. Et les anglais viennent gouverner la Lybie.\r\nCela a d tre sans lombre dun doute une priode difficile et dangereuse, o les choses les plus simples et sans prtention taient regardes avec soupon et inimiti. Arrigo est un jeune homme et pour ne pas subirsenfuit. Accroch avec une force enrage  lamarre dun bateau qui levait lancre (mon Dieu, quelle anxit!..), arrive  avec laide de Dieu,  Naples o la phrase  on recommence  zro  semble entrer dans les armes de la famille.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nLa vie est dure et pleine daventure, et les problmes ne tardent pas  arriver. Le gouvernement italien le pince sans passeport. Il ny a pas dissue: le service militaire est obligatoire. Par chance la guerre est finie!\r\nSeul, dans un pays quil ne connait quasiment pas, la famille encore en terre lointaine, ce nest pas facile, mais la volont  la tte dure: peut-tre lavenir derrire la porte sera-t-il plein de promesses fascinantes Ayant pay son dbit auprs de ltat et considrant le peu de perspectives immdiates quoffre notre pays martyris,  il migre en France et trouve du travail en tant que conducteur de tracteur  Nice. Ce nest pas mal et le climat y est bon  mais ce nest pas le top, pas pour Arrigo. Il veut plus. Laventure de derrire la porte lui fait de lil. Et Arrigo, toujours  la recherche de la fortune, part en Allemagne. LAllemagne a encore presque tout  reconstruire, du travail il y en a et Arrigo y rencontre Caterina.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nLa vie continue  mais les nouvelles de lAfrique ne sont pas consolantes. Le noyau familial Lorenzetto vit des moments difficiles. La Lybie est secoue de tumultes et de guerres locales, et la situation des ex-colonies deviennent toujours plus grave et plus pnible. Nereo Lorenzetto est peu  peu expropri de la terre quil avait travaille pendant tant dannes et o il avait lev sa famille. Un triste jour, lhistoire se conclue. La terre est perdue pour toujours\r\nIl ne reste que la vie, mme si dangereusement incertaine. Cest une dure ralit, injuste et cruelle. Grace  Dieu, un pays Nereo la. Ses racines sont en Italie et avec sa famille il fuit  non moins aventureusement vers sa terre natale. Et de nouveau on recommence  zro. Arrigo et ses frres sont maintenant unis par une mme impulsion. Albenga accueille le noyau fatigu et offre aux bras jeunes et robustes une possibilit de reprise. Pendant ce temps en Allemagne, Arrigo et Caterina saluent avec joie larrive de Germano, troisime gnration dune ligne daventuriers.\r\nOn y vit plutt bien dans ce grand pays malgr un climat rigoureux mais la nostalgie de la famille et de la terre natale se fait toujours plus pesante et finalement Arrigo retourne  Albenga De nouveau ils sont tous runis!\r\nLa moiti des annes 60 voyent les frres Lorenzetto cultiver un terrain en location et produisant des lgumes qui sont exports en Sude et en Allemagne. Travaillant dur, ils russissent  acheter un domaine  qui ensuite est vendu pour donner la possibilit  chaque nouvelle cellule familiale de commencer son envol en solitaire.\r\nEt encore une fois  on recommence  zro.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nLentement mais srement la terre donne ses fruits. On travaille, on pargne et on continue  acheter des lopins de terres en Ligurie. Arrigo dcide alors de construire une serre. Ayant foi en ce que la vie lui a enseign  cest  dire y mettre toute son nergie, il pense y arriver  la force de son poignet. Et il y arrive! Il cultive les tomates et les place facilement sur le march local. Mais il ne se sent pas encore pleinement ralis, pour utiliser un terme moderne.\r\n \r\nLe petit Germano et avec lui les justes ambitions dun pre, pourrait tre le titre de la suite des aventures. Dans les annes 70, Arrigo construit de nouveau une serre, cette fois-ci pas seule, et donne ainsi un tournant dcisif  son activit. Il commence  cultiver les gerberas en fleurs coupes. Nouveau travail, nouvelles expriences et beaucoup de satisfactions. La voix du milieu aura t  devine Pour la jeune entreprise, de 4 ans environ, souvre de nouvelles et attractives perspectives.\r\n \r\nIls cultivent les Dracaenas de diffrents types et les Yucca du Guatemala et du Costa-Rica sous les serres et les Eucalyptus en plein air, et il y a encore du terrain disponible... Linitiative plat  Germano et il commence  travailler dur, main dans la main avec son Pre Arrigo pour dvelopper encore et toujours lentreprise. Le projet prend forme et la transformation des cultures se dveloppe de pair avec la participation aux Salons dexpositions du secteur (Flormart  Padoue et Miflor  Milan).\r\n \r\nA travers et aprs toutes ces aventures, nous arrivons  notre poque\r\n \r\nLa Socit Lorenzetto SAS que nous connaissons aujourdhui comporte 20 000m2 de serres couvertes et 20 000 m2 de terres en plein air, produisant en serres couvertes de nombreuses plantes en pot typiques de la rgion mditerranenne  Cyclamens, Poinsettias et Chrysanthmes en automne et Lantaniers, Solanum Rantonetii et Anthmis au printemps; et un plein air ddi aux plantes aromatiques les plus connues et apprcies de toute lEurope.\r\nDes opportunits logistiques favorables et une collaboration de plus de 20 ans avec entre autre 240 tablissements floricoles ont contribus  largir les assortiments de plantes et donc leur pouvoir  satisfaire les demandes des clients.\r\n \r\nLes yeux toujours tourns sur le march, la Lorenzetto est aussi en mesure de fournir un grand choix de plantes siciliennes, profitant de 2 sites le sien  Albenga et lautre  Messina, afin de pouvoir excuter les commandes des lieux mme de production : Bougainville, Callistemon, Agrumes (orange, citron, mandarine, kumquat ), Laurier Rose, Phoenix, Cycas etc. - dans toutes les tailles et formes.\r\n \r\nCest pourquoi la Maison LORENZETTO est devenue un producteur-exportateur leader sur le march floricole international, travaillant avec de grandes enseignes. De plus ils suivent de prs lavance des recherches et maintiennent un dveloppement constant du systme floricole de production, de contrle de qualit et de prparation. lments qui leur permettent de vous offrir un produit de qualit et un service efficace et fiable. Voil ce quils peuvent vous garantir.\r\n</p>',1,12,'2014-01-02 13:27:38',591,'','2014-01-02 13:30:19',591,0,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2014-01-02 13:27:38','0000-00-00 00:00:00','{\"image_intro\":\"\",\"float_intro\":\"\",\"image_intro_alt\":\"\",\"image_intro_caption\":\"\",\"image_fulltext\":\"\",\"float_fulltext\":\"\",\"image_fulltext_alt